#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:12
# 3380d229eafe408f82a09d8ba4f6718c
msgid "The coordinate capture plugin is easy to use and provides the ability to display coordinates on the map canvas for two selected Coordinate Reference Systems (CRS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:27
# cde585bcb4114cdfa3a945fdbb526c50
msgid "Start QGIS, select |mActionOptions| :guilabel:`Project Properties` from the :guilabel:`Settings` (KDE, Windows) or :guilabel:`File` (Gnome, OSX) menu and click on the :guilabel:`Projection` tab. As an alternative you can also click on the |mIconProjectionEnabled| :sup:`CRS status` icon in the lower right-hand corner of the statusbar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:32
# 9b78cdb850ab4b38bb7ef67287dcca6a
msgid "Click on the |checkbox| `Enable on the fly projection` checkbox and select a projected coordinate system of your choice (see also :ref:`label_projections`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:34
# 9bda8c77d0e243dd8b1d9dcc9fafec49
msgid "Load the coordinate capture plugin in the Plugin Manager (see :ref:`load_core_plugin`) and ensure that the dialog is visible by going to :menuselection:`View --> Panels` and ensuring that |checkbox| :guilabel:`Coordinate Capture` is enabled. The coordinate capture dialog appears as shown in Figure figure_coordinate_capture_1_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:39
# 32b60381cef04a5ea39f3ddaac837af8
msgid "Click on the |geographic| :sup:`Click to the select the CRS to use for coordinate display` icon and select a different CRS from the one you selected above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:42
# f5605c87f91c4673bd1246b133c72ca3
msgid "To start capturing coordinates, click on **[Start capture]**. You can now click anywhere on the map canvas and the plugin will show the coordinates for both of your selected CRS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:45
# b411b13f967747ee8bdc312fcac931bf
msgid "To enable mouse coordinate tracking click the |tracking| :sup:`mouse tracking` icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:47
